		<description descriptionType="Abstract">The CM SAF Daylight Data Set is a satellite-based climatology derived from satellite-observations from the visible channel of the Meteosat satellites. The data are available from 1983 to 2011 and cover the region &#xB1;65&#xB0; longitude and &#xB1;65&#xB0; latitude. The products are available as monthly, and daily means on a regular latitude/longitude grid with a spatial resolution of 0.05&#xB0; x 0.05&#xB0; degrees.</description>
